body:
@ianlancetaylor they both have the same goal but the tap format is more widespread and will help us to use existing tools and it's covered by a spec.

@bradfitz sorry, I forgot to mention what TAP means.

I don't like colors too even tho I think the might be helpful for `diffing`. 

Having a standard output (covered by spec) and quite used in the industry helps to reusing existing tools (in this case reporters) already written, battle tested etc...

I imagine Google is pretty polyglot in terms of languages, so probably someone else already wrote a TAP to XML renderer for your testing systems. That's a guess!
